Heya, /hmofa/. I've decided to start a small slice of life story. This is half to build my skill with the genre, and half as something to do when inspiration isn't hitting for other projects. Updates probably won't be any longer than 2k words a pop, and it probably won't only be updated super often, but I thought I'd post regardless. The pic is some AI sloppa as a visual aid, and the name is subject to change.

>A displaced man himself in a world that is familiar, yet so, so alien... and pettable.
>Alien, however, doesn't mean bad, as shown by a fateful meeting.
>But even a redo of life in a sleepy village is not without its own particular hurdles
>A 2nd Person story starring (You) as Anonymous the human.

-------

>“Anon, honey, are you religious?”
>The kitchen knife in your hand pauses in its descent as you stop and think, leaving the plucked chicken on your cutting board whole for a little bit longer. Looking up, you see an angular face reflected in the glass door of the kitchen microwave.
>Humming thoughtfully, you wipe your greesy hands on your jeans and turn around, addressing the owner of the reflection. “What brought that question on?”
>Standing by the kitchen table next to a few baskets of sorted eggs is Jess, your girlfriend of several weeks.
>It’s been nearly a year since that fateful day you seemingly fell sideways through space. One moment, you were opening your front door after a long day at work, the next, you were falling out of the doorway of a broom closet.
>Needless to say, you were pretty shocked. The owners of the office building you seemingly teleported to were just as startled. To make things worse, you seemingly stumbled into some kind of office building staffed by freaks, because nearly all of the staff were wearing fur suits.
>… And then upon looking closer, you realized that those were not fur suits. Nine out of ten people were walking, talking animals.
>(Continued below).

>Tips on how to do this
shitty walkthrough dump

The game is split into five kingdoms.The top kingdom is the beast kingdom and is the 4th(?) kingdom you're meant to visit.

Most of the missions are already on the map though and it lets you tackle them early (it warns against this).
The mission to get the owl is a level 25 mission at the top right of the beast kingdom.

After the first area storyline you get the choice of either going to the ELF kingdom or the desert kingdom (areas 2 and 3).
Choose the desert kingdom because there is a coastal mission that if you beat and then rebuild the town, you get an early boat straight to the world 4 early.
Plus the first mission straight off the boat is her mission.

At this point I was level 18ish on average playing the game normally and was able to do both the 24 harbor mission and 25 beast mission to get her "early" by spamming items I stockpiled.

I played on the second highest difficulty, maybe you can get to her mission a lot faster through the orange route if you're waay lower level on an easier difficulty, idk. The orange route is a possible way to get her early around level 12-14. The red route is how I did it playing normally and got her right before the end of the area 2 storyline.

I also saved a mirror of appearance for her and changed her from a green to a white owl.

>does it fuck up your experience?
The game already gives you a strong as fuck way overleveled unit early and is balanced around having him. Adding Ramona to that squad doesn't really change much since she is a pure buff support and can't attack naturally.
